03997nam a22006375i 9786155225536DE-B159720220729113935.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220729t20222013hu     fo  d z      eng d  a97861552255367 a10.1515/97861552255362doi  a(DE-B1597)633414  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ahucHU 4aN 7aART0151102bisacsh1 aEşanu, Octavian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTransition in Post-Soviet Art :bThe Collective Actions Group Before and After 1989 /cOctavian Eşanu. 1aBudapest ;aNew York : bCentral European University Press, c[2022] 4c©2013  a1 online resource (376 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tList of Figures -- tCreating a Clearing: Foreword -- tPreface and Acknowledgments -- tPart I: A General Introduction to KD and Moscow Conceptualism -- tChapter 1. A Bibliographic Overview -- tChapter 2. Mapping Moscow Conceptualism -- tPart II: Transition: From KD to [KD] -- tChapter 3. KD’s Journeys Before 1989 -- tChapter 4. “During”: The Transition to Capitalism -- tChapter 5. [KD]’s Journeys After 1989 -- tAfterword: From KD to [KD]: From Objectivation to Reification -- tAppendix -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe artistic tradition that emerged as a form of cultural resistance in the 1970s changed during the transition from socialism to capitalism. This volume presents the evolution of the Moscow-based conceptual artist group called Collective Actions, proposing it as a case-study for understanding the transformations that took place in Eastern European art after the fall of the Berlin Wall. Esanu introduces Moscow Conceptualism by performing a close examination of the Collective Actions group's ten-volume publication Journeys Outside the City and of the Dictionary of Moscow Conceptualism. He analyzes above all the evolution of Collective Actions through ten consecutive phases, discussing changes that occur in each new volume of the Journeys. Compares the part of the Journeys produced in the Soviet period with those volumes assembled after the dissolution of the USSR. The concept of "transition" and the activities of Soros Centers for Contemporary Art are also analyzed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh  aCommunism, Conceptual art, Late 20th century, Moscow, Russia, Soviet Union, Transition.1 aGroys, Boris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978615522553640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155225536423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155225536/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK